              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9329315510199370877">Unfortunately, Dave Eggers got duped on this one. I found out from a GR connection who lives in New Orleans, where Zeitoun is a well-known as a scam artist via his contracting business. And when he was going around in his canoe, as described in the book, he was not rescuing people but burglarizing abandoned homes. This is why he was arrested, not because he was considered a terrorist. My connection mentioned that he had been recently arrested for beating his wife with a tire iron on a public str</span>
  <span id="freeText9329315510199370877" style="display:none">Unfortunately, Dave Eggers got duped on this one. I found out from a GR connection who lives in New Orleans, where Zeitoun is a well-known as a scam artist via his contracting business. And when he was going around in his canoe, as described in the book, he was not rescuing people but burglarizing abandoned homes. This is why he was arrested, not because he was considered a terrorist. My connection mentioned that he had been recently arrested for beating his wife with a tire iron on a public street.<br /><br />Update (2018).....<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.theadvocate.com/new_orleans/news/courts/article_7a5d0d0a-c2aa-11e8-b1bc-77f750860eeb.html">https://www.theadvocate.com/new_orlea...</a></span>
